description:
&lt;p&gt;Working closely within a team of Healthcare Assistants you will provide assistance to Radiographers, Sonographers and Radiology Consultants in a variety of clinical settings and imaging modalities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties of the role will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To assist Radiology staff during diagnostic imaging examinations, providing direct care, maintenance of equipment and administrative duties in order to ensure a high quality of service to patients across seven day working. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To provide cover on a rotational basis at Sunderland Royal Hospital and any other Trust facility, or satellite department which may be based at the local Primary Care Centres. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To assist in patient preparation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To act as patient chaperone.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To assist with patient documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is will be a demanding but very rewarding role, dealing with patients and staff inside and outside the Trust and requires excellent communication and interpersonal skills and a professional, friendly and approachable manner.  You will be working on a rotational basis and therefore required to provide cover which consistently meets service needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Radiology Department is open seven days per week, 24 hours per day.  You will therefore be required to work from 8.30 a.m. to 5.00 p.m. Monday to Friday, plus weekends and bank holidays as part of a rota.&lt;/p&gt;
